    Read the ReadMe.txt file and then follow the instructions to "Please read at least the "Installation" and "First Run" topics in JK-IDE.chm"

    "It uses a special build (compiled with VC10) of Scintilla as editing component. It has a new lexer and other additional code for Scintilla, therefore only scilexer.dll in this package will work properly (other scintilla builds don´t!). Be sure to have the VC10 runtimes installed, search for "vc 10 runtime X86 download", Microsoft offers a free download package. The VC 10 runtimes are not part of the IDE´s installation package, you must download and install them, if the IDE complains about missing dlls.
    ​"
    You need to instal the 32bi​t Visual C++ Runtime .
